{"atom_id": "ig34_p0285_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 285, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.6 Morphology (MO)", "atom_type": "NOTE", "verbatim": "Domain Decommissioning Update", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.3", "ts": "2026-04-27T01:49:12.330710Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0285_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 285, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.6 Morphology (MO)", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The MO domain has been decommissioned as of SDTMIG v3.4.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.3", "ts": "2026-04-27T01:49:12.330710Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0285_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 285, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.6 Morphology (MO)", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "When the Morphology domain was introduced in SDTMIG v3.2, the SDS Team planned to represent morphology and physiology findings in separate domains: morphology findings in the MO domain and physiology findings in separate domains by body systems.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.3", "ts": "2026-04-27T01:49:12.330710Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0285_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 285, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.6 Morphology (MO)", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Since then, the team found that separating morphology and physiology findings was more difficult than anticipated and provided little added value.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.3", "ts": "2026-04-27T01:49:12.330710Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0285_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 285, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.6 Morphology (MO)", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "This led to the decision to expand the body-system-based domains to cover both morphology and physiology findings and to deprecate MO in a future version of the SDTMIG.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.3", "ts": "2026-04-27T01:49:12.330710Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0285_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 285, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.6 Morphology (MO)", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Submissions using that later SDTMIG version would represent morphology results in the appropriate body-system-based physiology/morphology domain.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.3", "ts": "2026-04-27T01:49:12.330710Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0285_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 285, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.6 Morphology (MO)", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "For data prepared using a version of the SDTMIG that includes both the MO domain and body-system-based physiology/morphology domains, morphology findings may be represented in either the MO domain or in a body-system based physiology/morphology domain.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.3", "ts": "2026-04-27T01:49:12.330710Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0285_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 285, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.6 Morphology (MO)", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Custom body-system-based domains may be used if the appropriate body-system-based domain is not included in the SDTMIG version being used.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.3", "ts": "2026-04-27T01:49:12.330710Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0285_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 285, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3 [MODELS FOR FINDINGS DOMAINS]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "6.3.7 Morphology/Physiology Domains", "heading_level": 3, "sibling_index": 7, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.3", "ts": "2026-04-27T01:49:12.330710Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0285_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 285, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.7 Morphology/Physiology Domains", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Individual domains for morphology and physiology findings about specific body systems are grouped together in this section.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.3", "ts": "2026-04-27T01:49:12.330710Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0285_a021", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 285, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.7 Morphology/Physiology Domains", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "This grouping is not meant to imply that there is a single morphology/physiology domain.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.3", "ts": "2026-04-27T01:49:12.330710Z"}}
